Q.1>Write a Python program that calculates the area of a circle when the radius is provided by the user. Use π = 3.14 and display the area.
Input Format:
A single line containing a floating-point number representing the radius.
Output Format:
Print the computed area of the circle formatted to 4 decimal places

Code-

radius = float(input())
pi = 3.14
area = pi * radius * radius
print(f"{area:.4f}")

Q.2>Write a Python program to calculate the area of a rectangle given its length and width.

Code
